                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8 (PTI): The Supreme Court today directed the Centre to consider setting up a separate pay commission for both serving and retired personnel of the armed forces and slammed the government for forcing army personnel to run from pillar to post on salary disputes.          
	The court wanted to know if the Centre was open to the idea of a separate pay commission headed by a retired Chief Justice of India or an apex court judge.                  
	 Dewas (PTI): At least 16 people were killed when an overcrowded bus fell into the Bagdi river on Wednesday near Dewas in Madhya Pradesh. Seven people have been rescued so far. Efforts are on to pull the private bus out of the river.                  
	 Kochi (PTI): Kerala High Court on Wednesday dismissed the bail applications of seven Popular Front of India activists accused of involvement in the attack on a professor. T. J. Josephs palm had been slashed for preparing a question paper that allegedly hurt sentiments of the Muslim community.                   
	 Kollam (PTI): A man chopped off his wifes left palm during a quarrel at a village in Kollam, Kerala, on Tuesday night. Shocked villagers took Nasia, 31, to a hospital. Her husband, Hashim, 44, is absconding.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Maharashtra on Wednesday approved amendments to the State Transplantation of Human Organs Act, 1994, making organ donation more patient-friendly. Under the amended act, grandparents and grandchildren can also donate organs. Earlier, near relative who could donate organs included spouse, children, parents and siblings.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): Actor Shiney Ahujas maid has backtracked from her allegation that he raped her at his Mumbai residence last year. The 20-year-old said she had filed the complaint at the behest of the woman who had got her the job of a maid at Ahujas residence.
                                                                                                                                              
